Section1.Para:
The crystal structure of the STO substrate, as-deposited LSCO and BNBMT films were characterized by the X-ray diffractometry (D8 Focus, Bruker, Germany). The morphologies were observed by a field emission scanning electron microscopy (FESEM, S-4800, Hitachi, Japan). For electrical characterization, Au top electrodes with a diameter of 0.2 mm were prepared by dc sputtering. Dielectric constant (



                  $\varepsilon_{33}^{T}/\varepsilon_{0}$
                ) and loss (tan δ) of the films were measured using a precision impedance analyzer (Agilent HP4294A, Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA). The ferroelectric P-E loops and dc bias dependence of the capacitance were measured using a Sawyer-Tower circuit (TF2000 analyzer, Aixacct, Germany).
